# Spring Boot Ultimate Production Rules - Testing (5 Rules)

1. All business logic in services and domain components must have unit tests.
2. Integration tests must validate real database behavior for critical repositories and transactions.
3. Critical business flows must have end-to-end tests covering success and failure paths.
4. Enforce minimum line/branch coverage above 80 percent for backend modules.
5. Tests must be deterministic, isolated, and runnable in CI without external manual dependencies.

# Spring Boot Ultimate Production Rules - CI/CD (5 Rules)

6. Block merges unless CI passes all mandatory quality gates.
7. CI pipeline must include build, unit tests, integration tests, and static analysis.
8. Fail pipeline on security scanning or quality gate violations above defined thresholds.
9. Build immutable Docker images and deploy via versioned, traceable artifacts.
10. Require progressive deployment checks (health, rollback trigger, and post-deploy verification).
